---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="Context header for sidecar AI — Harwell Prompt Engineering"
  pageDescription="Paste this header above your code when using browser-based AI alongside an IDE so the model knows your environment."
  showSocials={false}
>
  <article class="course-page handout-page">
    <header>
      <p class="course-breadcrumb"><a href="/courses/harwell-ai">Harwell — Prompt Engineering</a></p>
      <h1>Context header for sidecar AI</h1>
    </header>

    <p>
      When you use a <strong>browser-based AI</strong> (e.g. ChatGPT, Copilot) alongside
      an IDE that doesn't have AI built in, paste this header <strong>above</strong> your
      code so the model knows your environment. Then paste your code and ask your question.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Copy-paste template</h2>
      <pre class="handout-pre"><code>Context:
- Framework: Spring Boot 3
- Java version: 17
- Style: Constructor injection (no @Autowired)
- Testing: JUnit 5, Mockito
- Database: JPA/Hibernate

Code:
[Paste your code here]

Question: [Your question]</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Customise for your project</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Change <strong>Framework</strong> and <strong>Java version</strong> to match your stack.</li>
        <li>Add <strong>Style</strong> rules (e.g. "No Optional in public API", "Use records for DTOs").</li>
        <li>Add <strong>Testing</strong> (e.g. "JUnit 5, AssertJ").</li>
        <li>Add <strong>Database</strong> or other tech (e.g. "PostgreSQL", "MongoDB").</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why use it?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Without context, the AI gives <strong>generic</strong> answers that may not match your codebase.</li>
        <li>With this header, you get answers that respect your stack and style and reduce back-and-forth.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p class="handout-footer">
      From the Harwell Prompt Engineering course (Module 4 — Tooling strategies).
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .course-page {
    max-width: 90ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .handout-page .course-breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .handout-page .course-breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--site-green);
  }

  .handout-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--site-green);
  }

  .handout-page section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .handout-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .handout-pre {
    background: rgba(0, 105, 46, 0.08);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--site-green);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .handout-pre code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .handout-footer {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
